description:
Our client is a Listed group,  Current they are looking for potential candidate to join their Finance team in Hong Kong.

Responsibilities;

Report to Head of Finance (General Account & Finance Analysis);
To Lead a small team of Finance Operation Team in Hong Kong;

Handle full set of account including operaton /finance analysis/ management account etc;
To perform and lead the accounting process and procedure, ensuring compliance with the accounting policies and guidelines;
Lead and coaching to a small team to manage accounting reporting & reporting;
Good communcation with English and Chinese is must.
Requirements:

Degree or Above in Accounting or related discipline;

Holder of CPA professional qualification and experience in 4A CPA Firm is a plus;
About 8+  years working experience in Full set of accounting and Management Accounting;
Experience in Multi-national group is preferred;
Solid Experience in Asia Pacific Trading Business is preferred;
Good experience in dealing with various country business user;
Using software with MS Office (Execl, Word, Powerpoint) and Oracle Finance is a plus;
Excellent spoken and written communication skill in English;
Work independently and good team leadership.
Our client will offer competitive remuneration package and good career prospects to the potential candidate, interested parties please quote ref.no.FM-0117-sh-JDB and submit your resume to Ms Fung by our email or enquiry with Tel:3428-6121.


All profiles are handled with strictest confidentiality. Shortlisted candidates would be notified

Job Responsibilities:

Perform all general accounting duties and operations;
Prepare financial report;
Prepare consolidated accounting statements;
Prepare monthly/quarterly management report;
Assist in any other ad-hoc assignments when necessary 

Requirements:

Bachelor degree in accounting or other related area;
At least 6 years' relevant experience;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Independent, initiative, detail-minded and well-organized;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese, able to speak Mandarin
Interact with external auditor and banks
IMMEDIATELY AVAILABLE is highly preferred

 Attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits will be given to the successful candidate.  Please send your full resume with current and expected salary via email to hr-hk@enicar.com.

***PLEASE DO NOT USE QUICK APPLY FUNCTION***

