Responsibilities                        

Business support on project financial reviews, highlight the project risks, issuance of invoices and credit notes and following up debt status;
Monitor sub-consultancy payments;
Assist in month-end, year-end closing and management reports;
Conduct financial analysis for business unit performance;
Prepare annual budget, quarterly forecast and management analysis;
Prepare presentation and relevant materials for management meeting;
Monitoring e-timesheet record; and
Participate in ad hoc projects as assigned.

Qualification Requirements   

Degree in Accounting or related disciplines with professional qualifications in HKICPA/ACCA or equivalent;
At least 5 years relevant working experiences, preferably from MNC;
Mature, responsible and able to work under pressure;
Good work attitude, well organized and highly systematic;
Attentive to details and strong analytical mind;
Strong PC skills & familiar with Microsoft Office;
Knowledge in JDE and Hyperion would be preferred;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese; and
Immediately available is an advantage.
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Accountant

Responsibilities:

To assist in overseeing and preparing month end accounts closing and consolidation, financial and management report, forecast and financial analysis;
To liaise with auditors, tax representatives and professionals regarding audit, tax and other relevant matters;
To work closely with the Singapore team to ensure all transactions are recognized accurately and timely;
To co-ordinate with operation and internal IT teams on daily operations and to help solving work related issues;
To handle tax filing;
To assist in company secretarial matters; and
To work with development team to enhance the financial consolidation system
To handle ad hoc assignment as requested.

Requirements:

University graduate in Finance or Accounting with professional accounting qualification;
Minimum 2 years working experience, with Big 4 background;
Solid experience in Singapore IRAS compliance is an advantage;
Out-going, independent, self-motivated, strong interpersonal and communication skills, can work under pressure;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Cantonese;
Infrequent travel to Singapore is required;
Candidates who have less experience will be considered as Accountant.

